PSI issues

PAT version change
  -> resnoop PAT, update PMT pid table (no in/out sync issue)

PMT version change
  -> resnoop PMT, update input/output pid tables (sync issue)

MPTS PMT pid table merging
  -> Progressively build input/output PID tables
  -> add new program's PID into existing PID table
  We can solve the reorder problem by storing pid_idx in pid_table also.
  This will make the update very efficient!


Type of PID table change:
Adding new PIDs:
  - need for MPTS PMT snooping
  - can be handled by storing pid_idx in pid_table also.

Deleting PIDs:


Note: since we used a fixed mapping between program number and output PIDs,
      a lot can be simplifed.
      => No need to sync output pid table with input pid table!!
Note: The above observation may not be quite right for MPTS.

Note: Input PID table can be reorder for lookup performance.

      As long as output PID table is not reshuffled, no need to worry about
      input/output resync.

      For PMT table, as long as we reuse the slots in the output pid table
      it would be fine!
      For reuse purpose, we need to mark a PID being not used.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
To simplify things, we will try to do the following:

- input PSI snooping done in the input thread
- input thread will explicitly look for PAT, PMT(s) from pmt_pid_table,
  and other PIDs from in_pid_table
- Only one version of pmt_pid_table and in_pid_table for in_session.
  Only one version of out_pid_table for out_session.

